{
  "stem": "27335.8",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Against the Tel Aviv radio, that they used his name-- that they used his name.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But not really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no, but Sass spoke to him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE] to, if he ever meets me again to apologize, because he had nothing to do with me, and he demanded from the radio station that they distract it, because he doesn't know me.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they never did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we had another incident where I was in a Hungarian military history institute, a history institute, and they were interviewing me, a woman about your size and so on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A colonel-- he was second in command.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And to be sure that they wanted to document everything, she sent down a message to Israel to the military institute there, military history, and the-- they reply was this-- your man-- your man is an imposter.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Hannah Szenes was never in British service.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was sent there by the Zionists, the Palestine Zionists at the time to liberate the Jews-- this kind of nonsense.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had to make a point about this in my book, you see.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They even denied that he was in British-- British service, that he volunteered.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "By Christ, what it took for the British to find her and find me, and the [INAUDIBLE] people selected, people that trained them, with all the expenses and so on, and this-- this [INAUDIBLE] people they they-- she wasn't in-- even in a British service.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I tried to.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was really anxious, because Palgi and Goldstein-- Goldstein they-- landed in Kasztner's office, you see, and they inquired about Hannah Szenes-- was she reported to you.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They didn't know about Kasztner.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Kasztner used them for a while, [INAUDIBLE], and finally he threw them-- not only them, but there were other-- the two artists.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
